00:11:26,180 --> 00:11:27,700
 He is just as unfathomable,

265
00:11:27,700 --> 00:11:31,700
 He is just as uncontainable as He claims He is, right?

266
00:11:31,700 --> 00:11:35,060
 If God was actually able to be pinned down by you,

267
00:11:35,060 --> 00:11:37,780
 the Almighty, when you were in your teenage years,

268
00:11:37,780 --> 00:11:39,580
 is that a God worth following?

269
00:11:39,580 --> 00:11:44,920
 No, like no one here is rocking Nike Elites

270
00:11:44,920 --> 00:11:47,180
 and Sperry's tonight, I wouldn't guess.

271
00:11:47,180 --> 00:11:51,300
 And the reason why is you've likely outgrown them.

272
00:11:51,300 --> 00:11:52,700
 But with that said,

273
00:11:52,700 --> 00:11:56,060
 does that mean that you've outgrown the need for shoes?

274
00:11:56,060 --> 00:11:58,300
 No, I'd guess that your shoe game

275
00:11:58,300 --> 00:12:00,000
 is at its very best right now.

276
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:04,140
 The same has to happen when it comes to our faith.

277
00:12:04,140 --> 00:12:07,460
 We have to be willing to look at our doubts

278
00:12:07,460 --> 00:12:10,020
 and not allow them to lead us further from God,

279
00:12:10,020 --> 00:12:13,220
 but allow them to lead us further into God.

280
00:12:13,220 --> 00:12:15,700
 And so I'm really excited because some of you are here,

281
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:18,500
 you're wrestling and yet God's like,

282
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:22,220
 "Oh baby, we're about to go deep.

283
00:12:22,220 --> 00:12:24,620
 "I'm about to take you to a new level of understanding.

284
00:12:24,620 --> 00:12:27,280
 "I'm about to take you to a new place of faith.

285
00:12:27,280 --> 00:12:30,700
 "I'm about to stir up something new in your spirit."

286
00:12:30,700 --> 00:12:31,540
 Are you ready?

287
00:12:31,540 --> 00:12:34,060
 That's what God wants to do.

288
00:12:34,060 --> 00:12:37,360
 That's his heart and I love the enthusiasm.

289
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:42,740
 A.J. Swoboda in his book "After Doubt" said it like this.

290
00:12:42,740 --> 00:12:45,800
 He said, "There's often no greater act of faith

291
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:49,800
 "in fidelity to God than bearing one's deepest held beliefs

292
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:54,380
 "to divine criticism so that God might be loved more."

293
00:12:54,380 --> 00:12:56,540
 To put it simply, kicking the tires

294
00:12:56,540 --> 00:12:58,620
 doesn't mean you hate the car.

295
00:12:58,620 --> 00:13:03,620
 You see, doubt, it's not the enemy of your affections

296
00:13:03,620 --> 00:13:04,560
 for God.

297
00:13:04,560 --> 00:13:08,060
 Doubt is the opportunity to love God more,

298
00:13:08,060 --> 00:13:13,340
 to find answers that not only satisfy your questions,

299
00:13:13,340 --> 00:13:15,100
 but satisfy your souls.

300
00:13:15,100 --> 00:13:19,080
 That's what I wanna talk to you about tonight.

301
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:20,700
 And in order for us to do it,

302
00:13:20,700 --> 00:13:24,380
 we're gonna look at a passage in the gospel of Luke.

303
00:13:24,380 --> 00:13:26,700
 So if you have a Bible, you can pull it out

304
00:13:26,700 --> 00:13:29,540
 and turn with me to Luke chapter 24.

305
00:13:29,540 --> 00:13:33,020
 As you do that, I wanna set up some context,

306
00:13:33,020 --> 00:13:35,180
 not just to fill the gap as you flip the pages,

307
00:13:35,180 --> 00:13:36,580
 but to really set something up

308
00:13:36,580 --> 00:13:37,780
 that I think will be helpful to you

309
00:13:37,780 --> 00:13:39,780
 because this idea of deconstruction

310
00:13:39,780 --> 00:13:42,020
 is not an idea that is new to Jesus.

311
00:13:42,020 --> 00:13:44,100
 It's something that he actually dealt with repeatedly

312
00:13:44,100 --> 00:13:45,780
 over the course of his ministry.

313
00:13:45,780 --> 00:13:47,580
 And he cared a great deal about

314
00:13:47,580 --> 00:13:49,780
 because when we come to this passage in Luke chapter 24,

315
00:13:49,780 --> 00:13:53,260
 what we need to know is Jesus is right on the heels

316
00:13:53,260 --> 00:13:56,340
 of his resurrection, yet he has not yet gone to the father.

317
00:13:56,340 --> 00:14:00,020
 He has not yet ascended back to heaven.

318
00:14:00,020 --> 00:14:02,100
 And all throughout this 40 day window

319
00:14:02,100 --> 00:14:04,040
 that he has between the resurrection and the ascension,

320
00:14:04,040 --> 00:14:06,520
 Jesus keeps making special guest appearances

321
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:07,540
 all across the Holy land.

322
00:14:07,540 --> 00:14:09,740
 He makes cameos in the most unlikely of places

323
00:14:09,740 --> 00:14:12,220
 because if you were him and I were him,

324
00:14:12,220 --> 00:14:13,740
 what would we likely do?

325
00:14:13,740 --> 00:14:16,540
 We'd probably show up and rebuke the religious elite.

326
00:14:16,540 --> 00:14:18,340
 Hey, you guys, what were you thinking?

327
00:14:18,340 --> 00:14:20,740
 We would probably show up and we would confront the Romans.

328
00:14:20,740 --> 00:14:21,660
 You crucified me, man.

329
00:14:21,660 --> 00:14:22,780
 What were you thinking?

330
00:14:22,780 --> 00:14:24,220
 Jesus doesn't do that.

331
00:14:24,220 --> 00:14:26,540
 He doesn't go to the religious elite.

332
00:14:26,540 --> 00:14:27,940
 He doesn't go to the Romans.

333
00:14:27,940 --> 00:14:32,380
 Instead, what Jesus does is he pursues the doubtful.

334
00:14:32,380 --> 00:14:36,740
 That's his mission in this 40 day window.

335
00:14:36,740 --> 00:14:41,740
 It's to restore the faith of the faint hearted.

336
00:14:41,740 --> 00:14:45,080
 He goes to Mary.

337
00:14:45,080 --> 00:14:47,620
 He comes to Thomas.

338
00:14:47,620 --> 00:14:48,980
 He restores Peter.

339
00:14:48,980 --> 00:14:51,260
 He appears in the upper room.

340
00:14:51,260 --> 00:14:55,560
 And right here, he walks with two disciples

341
00:14:55,560 --> 00:14:58,220
 down a road to Emmaus.

342
00:14:58,220 --> 00:15:00,900
 So it says this in Luke chapter 24.

343
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:02,700
 We'll pick it up in verse 13.

344
00:15:02,700 --> 00:15:08,220
 That very day, two of them were going

345
00:15:08,220 --> 00:15:10,440
 to a village named Emmaus,

346
00:15:10,440 --> 00:15:11,860
 about seven miles from Jerusalem.

347
00:15:11,860 --> 00:15:13,300
 And they were talking with each other

348
00:15:13,300 --> 00:15:14,780
 about all these things that had happened.

349
00:15:14,780 --> 00:15:16,740
 While they were talking and discussing together,

350
00:15:16,740 --> 00:15:19,820
 Jesus himself drew near and he went with them.

351
00:15:19,820 --> 00:15:22,180
 But their eyes were kept from recognizing him.

352
00:15:22,180 --> 00:15:24,340
 And he said to them,

353
00:15:24,340 --> 00:15:26,620
 what is this conversation that you're having

354
00:15:26,620 --> 00:15:29,300
 or that you're holding with each other as you walk?

355
00:15:29,300 --> 00:15:31,740
 And they stood still looking sad.

356
00:15:31,740 --> 00:15:33,980
 Then one of them named Cleopas answered him,

357
00:15:33,980 --> 00:15:36,660
 are you the only visitor to Jerusalem

358
00:15:36,660 --> 00:15:37,700
 who does not know the things

359
00:15:37,700 --> 00:15:39,540
 that have happened here in these days?

360
00:15:39,540 --> 00:15:41,260
 And he said to them, what things?

361
00:15:41,260 --> 00:15:43,740
 And they said to him, concerning Jesus of Nazareth,

362
00:15:43,740 --> 00:15:46,020
 a man who was a prophet, mighty indeed,

363
00:15:46,020 --> 00:15:47,780
 and word before God and all the people,

364
00:15:47,780 --> 00:15:49,300
 and how our chief priests and rulers

365
00:15:49,300 --> 00:15:52,140
 delivered him up to be condemned to death and crucified him.

366
00:15:52,140 --> 00:15:54,500
 But we had hoped that he was the one to redeem Israel.

367
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:56,020
 Yes, and besides all this,

368
00:15:56,020 --> 00:15:59,060
 it's now the third day since these things have happened.

369
00:15:59,060 --> 00:16:01,300
 That comment at the end, it's now the third day,

370
00:16:01,300 --> 00:16:03,700
 it means that they're at a moment of incredible discouragement

371
00:16:03,700 --> 00:16:08,380
 because it was the point at which the Jewish mind

372
00:16:08,380 --> 00:16:10,760
 thought that the soul would leave the body upon death.

373
00:16:10,760 --> 00:16:11,600
 Day three.

374
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:13,660
 So it's interesting.

375
00:16:13,660 --> 00:16:15,700
 Whenever you read the resurrection appearances of Jesus

376
00:16:15,700 --> 00:16:17,120
 at the end of the gospels,

377
00:16:17,120 --> 00:16:21,620
 what you find is he not only repeatedly appears to people,

378
00:16:21,620 --> 00:16:25,180
 but he constantly conceals his identity.

379
00:16:25,180 --> 00:16:26,660
 He's got a flair for the dramatic.

380
00:16:26,660 --> 00:16:28,500
 He likes a grand entrance.

381
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:31,100
 We find that three different times,

382
00:16:31,100 --> 00:16:33,140
 he conceals his identity.

383
00:16:33,140 --> 00:16:36,620
 He comes to Mary and he presents himself as a gardener.

384
00:16:36,620 --> 00:16:39,300
 He comes to Peter and the seven disciples,

385
00:16:39,300 --> 00:16:42,020
 and he looks like a man sitting on shore beside the fire.

386
00:16:42,020 --> 00:16:43,020
 And then in this moment,

387
00:16:43,020 --> 00:16:44,260
 he looks like a fellow wanderer

388
00:16:44,260 --> 00:16:48,500
 to both Cleopas and his companion on the road to Emmaus,

389
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:49,820
 which begs the question, why?

390
00:16:49,820 --> 00:16:54,700
 Why does Jesus conceal his identity in these moments?

391
00:16:54,700 --> 00:16:57,740
 Well, scholars, they have a variety of different answers

392
00:16:57,740 --> 00:16:58,980
 that no one knows for sure.

393
00:16:58,980 --> 00:17:00,620
 Some scholars look at it and they say,

394
00:17:00,620 --> 00:17:02,940
 this is going to be the method of Jesus's primary ministry

395
00:17:02,940 --> 00:17:03,900
 once he ascends to heaven.

396
00:17:03,900 --> 00:17:07,060
 It's going to be communicated through common men.

397
00:17:07,060 --> 00:17:09,140
 And so he wants to be a common man

398
00:17:09,140 --> 00:17:11,700
 that is communicating to other common men.

399
00:17:11,700 --> 00:17:12,860
 That's why he conceals his identity.

400
00:17:12,860 --> 00:17:14,060
 Other people look at it and say,

401
00:17:14,060 --> 00:17:15,500
 it's because of the disbelief of those

402
00:17:15,500 --> 00:17:16,380
 that he's appearing to.

403
00:17:16,380 --> 00:17:19,420
 He's looking at them and they cannot see him for who he is

404
00:17:19,420 --> 00:17:21,940
 because they don't believe completely.

405
00:17:21,940 --> 00:17:24,820
 Others say that he is supernaturally concealing his identity.

406
00:17:24,820 --> 00:17:27,720
 He's throwing up a spiritual mask

407
00:17:27,720 --> 00:17:30,020
 to conceal himself from these others.

408
00:17:30,020 --> 00:17:30,980
 Others look at him and say,

409
00:17:30,980 --> 00:17:32,420
 it's just a physical obstruction.

410
00:17:32,420 --> 00:17:33,320
 He's too far away.

411
00:17:33,320 --> 00:17:36,140
 They can't make out the details of his face.

412
00:17:36,140 --> 00:17:40,040
 We don't know why he conceals his identity ultimately.

413
00:17:40,040 --> 00:17:43,460
 And yet, as I peeled through these pages

414
00:17:43,460 --> 00:17:44,780
 and poured over and study,

415
00:17:44,780 --> 00:17:47,220
 I think I arrived at a hunch that's pretty unique.

416
00:17:47,220 --> 00:17:51,220
 I think that Jesus conceals his identity repeatedly

417
00:17:51,220 --> 00:17:54,060
 in these moments because he wants to,

418
00:17:54,060 --> 00:17:57,780
 he wants to engage with people

419
00:17:57,780 --> 00:18:02,680
 at the level of their rawest emotion.

420
00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:05,540
 Like that's what you see.

421
00:18:05,540 --> 00:18:07,820
 Like Jesus conceals his identity and he comes to Mary

422
00:18:07,820 --> 00:18:09,340
 and what he sees is that she's sorrowful.

423
00:18:09,340 --> 00:18:10,880
 He conceals his identity and he comes to Peter

424
00:18:10,880 --> 00:18:12,240
 and he sees that he's shameful.

425
00:18:12,240 --> 00:18:14,480
 He conceals his identity and he comes to these two guys

426
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:16,680
 and he sees that they're disappointed.

427
00:18:16,680 --> 00:18:19,140
 By way of him hiding who he is,

428
00:18:19,140 --> 00:18:21,660
 we can actually see who they are.

429
00:18:21,660 --> 00:18:25,480
 He wants to engage people at an emotional level.

430
00:18:25,480 --> 00:18:27,320
 So much so that it says in this passage

431
00:18:27,320 --> 00:18:29,720
 that they stood still looking sad

432
00:18:29,720 --> 00:18:33,040
 because they had hoped that he was the one to redeem Israel.

433
00:18:33,040 --> 00:18:35,720
 And yet, because he did live up to that expectation,

434
00:18:35,720 --> 00:18:37,600
 according to their estimation,

435
00:18:38,800 --> 00:18:40,880
 they are walking away from him entirely.

436
00:18:40,880 --> 00:18:47,560
 Their doubt has descended to such a place

437
00:18:47,560 --> 00:18:52,920
 that they're bailing on this whole way of Christ altogether.

438
00:18:52,920 --> 00:18:55,920
 And yet Jesus comes to them and he reveals to us

439
00:18:55,920 --> 00:18:59,060
 the very first thing he does is he restores the doubtful.

440
00:18:59,060 --> 00:19:01,400
 Jesus walks with those who are walking away.

441
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:04,560
 Jesus walks with those who are walking away.

442
00:19:04,560 --> 00:19:08,880
 That's the first way he pursues those downcast in doubt.

443
00:19:08,880 --> 00:19:10,800
 These guys are sad, they're disappointed.

444
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:12,640
 They're probably headed to Emmaus

445
00:19:12,640 --> 00:19:13,760
 for a little bit of self-care.

446
00:19:13,760 --> 00:19:17,800
 The city was known for being a place of natural hot springs.

447
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:19,120
 And so they think that's probably nice

448
00:19:19,120 --> 00:19:21,120
 after everything that they've lived through.

449
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:23,740
 And yet what we know is because they're on the way to Emmaus,

450
00:19:23,740 --> 00:19:25,880
 they are not huddled with the other disciples

451
00:19:25,880 --> 00:19:26,960
 in the upper room.

452
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:30,320
 They're not gathered with the women by the tomb.

453
00:19:30,320 --> 00:19:32,320
 They're not even hiding in Jerusalem

454
00:19:32,320 --> 00:19:34,720
 or waiting for some new development in the story.

455
00:19:34,720 --> 00:19:36,680
 No, they have given up.

456
00:19:36,680 --> 00:19:38,520
 They are walking away.

457
00:19:38,520 --> 00:19:42,140
 They have chosen to move on with their life.

458
00:19:42,140 --> 00:19:44,540
 And while it would be easy for us on this side of the cross

459
00:19:44,540 --> 00:19:47,040
 to look at them and shake our head and wag our finger,

460
00:19:47,040 --> 00:19:48,200
 how dare you guys?

461
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:50,160
 We do this ourselves.

462
00:19:50,160 --> 00:19:55,080
 We walk away from Jesus for all sorts of different reasons,

463
00:19:55,080 --> 00:19:56,560
 even good reasons.

464
00:19:56,560 --> 00:19:59,840
 Like some of us, we walk away from the faith

465
00:19:59,840 --> 00:20:03,380
 because we've been hurt by the church.

466
00:20:03,380 --> 00:20:06,160
 Others of us walk away because we've been slandered

467
00:20:06,160 --> 00:20:08,520
 and belittled by other Christians.

468
00:20:08,520 --> 00:20:11,840
 We walk away from the church because we look at the pulpit

469
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:14,200
 and think it's become a place of political theater

470
00:20:14,200 --> 00:20:16,080
 over the course of the last two election cycles

471
00:20:16,080 --> 00:20:17,900
 and eight years altogether.

472
00:20:17,900 --> 00:20:20,640
 We walk away from the church because God claims to be good

473
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:22,040
 and yet he let me down.

474
00:20:22,040 --> 00:20:23,920
 He didn't show up when I needed him most.

475
00:20:23,920 --> 00:20:25,900
 We walk away from the church

476
00:20:25,900 --> 00:20:28,880
 because there are other truth claims out there

477
00:20:28,880 --> 00:20:31,280
 that seem to make better sense of my reality,

478
00:20:31,280 --> 00:20:35,940
 that seem to help explain my experience.

479
00:20:35,940 --> 00:20:39,280
 Like we all have our reasons for walking away,

480
00:20:39,280 --> 00:20:41,200
 even good reasons for doing so.

481
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:46,160
 And yet Jesus is anything but reasonable.

482
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:50,680
 He's anything but reasonable.

483
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:52,360
 That's what Paul says in Romans chapter five.

484
00:20:52,360 --> 00:20:54,400
 He says, "For while we were still weak,

485
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:57,380
 "at the right time, Christ died for the ungodly.

486
00:20:57,380 --> 00:21:00,260
 "For one will scarcely die for a righteous person,

487
00:21:00,260 --> 00:21:02,240
 "though perhaps for a good person, one would dare to die."

488
00:21:02,240 --> 00:21:04,220
 Do you see, do you hear Paul reasoning?

489
00:21:04,220 --> 00:21:07,840
 But God shows his love for us

490
00:21:07,840 --> 00:21:10,640
 in that while we were still sinners, Christ died for us.

491
00:21:10,640 --> 00:21:13,960
 He does the most unreasonable thing.

492
00:21:13,960 --> 00:21:17,040
 Like he loves his enemies and he forgives his adversaries

493
00:21:17,040 --> 00:21:19,680
 and he gives of himself without any expectation

494
00:21:19,680 --> 00:21:20,960
 of anything in return.

495
00:21:20,960 --> 00:21:22,680
 He dies a death he does not deserve.

496
00:21:22,680 --> 00:21:24,160
 He rises from the grave.

497
00:21:24,160 --> 00:21:25,400
 Who does that?

498
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:27,980
 He tells us, "Hey, seek after me,"

499
00:21:27,980 --> 00:21:30,140
 when none of us are worthy of seeking after him.

500
00:21:30,140 --> 00:21:34,580
 And ultimately he walks with us when we walk away from him.

501
00:21:34,580 --> 00:21:36,740
 This is who our Jesus is.

502
00:21:36,740 --> 00:21:38,520
 So let me ask you, if you're here tonight

503
00:21:38,520 --> 00:21:42,360
 and you're doubting Jesus, then what are you walking towards?

504
00:21:42,360 --> 00:21:46,740
 Like they're not just walking away from Jerusalem

505
00:21:46,740 --> 00:21:49,340
 and all the doubt and all the disappointment

506
00:21:49,340 --> 00:21:50,820
 that was there behind them.

507
00:21:50,820 --> 00:21:53,140
 They are actually walking towards Emmaus.

508
00:21:53,140 --> 00:21:54,600
 So it begs the question for us,

509
00:21:54,600 --> 00:21:55,780
 where is it that we're walking?

510
00:21:55,780 --> 00:21:56,860
 Where are you going?

511
00:21:56,860 --> 00:21:59,820
 Are you walking towards romance?

512
00:21:59,820 --> 00:22:04,020
 Are you walking towards success or comfort,

513
00:22:04,020 --> 00:22:06,700
 power, approval, money?

514
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:08,500
 Like what is it that you're walking towards?

515
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:12,220
 And I don't ask you that because I want to shame you

516
00:22:12,220 --> 00:22:13,620
 with respect to where you're walking.

517
00:22:13,620 --> 00:22:16,860
 I ask you that because wherever it is you're walking,

518
00:22:16,860 --> 00:22:19,120
 there it is that Jesus is going to find you.

519
00:22:19,120 --> 00:22:23,560
 He meets them on this road and he will meet you

520
00:22:23,560 --> 00:22:25,940
 on whatever road it is you're walking.

521
00:22:25,940 --> 00:22:28,460
 Not because he wants you to get there,

522
00:22:28,460 --> 00:22:33,020
 but because he wants to get you back to him.

523
00:22:33,020 --> 00:22:34,940
 That's what he's gonna do.

524
00:22:34,940 --> 00:22:36,580
