00:34:50,020 --> 00:34:52,940
 I don't believe any of the same things as them.

788
00:34:52,940 --> 00:34:55,660
 Like, yes, Jesus wants a relationship with them,

789
00:34:55,660 --> 00:34:56,820
 but I look nothing like them.

790
00:34:56,820 --> 00:35:00,500
 And so therefore, Jesus wants nothing to do with me.

791
00:35:00,500 --> 00:35:04,620
 If that's you and you hear all of this

792
00:35:04,620 --> 00:35:06,820
 and you know all your doubt

793
00:35:06,820 --> 00:35:09,440
 and you feel like you don't fit into the story,

794
00:35:09,440 --> 00:35:13,920
 then you need to know.

795
00:35:13,920 --> 00:35:17,260
 While we know the name of one disciple, Cleopas,

796
00:35:17,260 --> 00:35:22,640
 we do not know the name nor identity of the other.

797
00:35:22,640 --> 00:35:28,660
 That disciple, he or she, is known as the unknown disciple.

798
00:35:28,660 --> 00:35:32,460
 And the reason it is is because Luke wants those

799
00:35:32,460 --> 00:35:34,980
 that feel like this could never be their story

800
00:35:34,980 --> 00:35:38,340
 to find themselves in the story.

801
00:35:38,340 --> 00:35:44,500
 He wants you to know there's no one that Jesus doesn't want.

802
00:35:44,500 --> 00:35:50,020
 There's no person that Jesus doesn't desire.

803
00:35:50,020 --> 00:35:53,500
 Doesn't matter the depth or the degree of your doubt,

804
00:35:53,500 --> 00:35:55,780
 this story is telling us that Jesus

805
00:35:55,780 --> 00:36:00,420
 doesn't just want to build in us an unbreakable belief.

806
00:36:00,420 --> 00:36:05,300
 He wants to build in us an unbreakable bond,

807
00:36:05,300 --> 00:36:08,780
 one that can never be broken.

808
00:36:08,780 --> 00:36:15,580
 So several years ago, I learned this lesson very personally

809
00:36:15,580 --> 00:36:18,540
 when I endured what felt like the greatest

810
00:36:18,540 --> 00:36:21,420
 personal challenge of my life to that point.

811
00:36:21,420 --> 00:36:24,540
 It was one of those dark nights of the soul sort of moments.

812
00:36:24,540 --> 00:36:27,180
 Some of you get what I'm talking about.

813
00:36:27,180 --> 00:36:31,220
 I was standing at the precipice of a new job opportunity

814
00:36:31,220 --> 00:36:33,180
 that was the stuff of my dreams.

815
00:36:33,180 --> 00:36:36,340
 Like it was the very thing that I had secretly wished for,

816
00:36:36,340 --> 00:36:37,900
 journaled about, prayed to God,

817
00:36:37,900 --> 00:36:42,140
 yet never admitted allowed to because it was so ridiculous.

818
00:36:42,140 --> 00:36:44,540
 It was so audacious.

819
00:36:44,540 --> 00:36:47,540
 And yet like I found myself in the throes of a new,

820
00:36:47,540 --> 00:36:51,820
 in the throes of actually attaining it.

821
00:36:54,420 --> 00:36:56,860
 And so I found in that season,

822
00:36:56,860 --> 00:36:58,460
 like I was closer to God than ever

823
00:36:58,460 --> 00:37:00,580
 because I needed God more than ever.

824
00:37:00,580 --> 00:37:03,420
 Like I was religiously, regularly going

825
00:37:03,420 --> 00:37:04,900
 on prayer walks with God.

826
00:37:04,900 --> 00:37:08,420
 Get out of the house and I would go

827
00:37:08,420 --> 00:37:10,420
 for long stretches of my day.

828
00:37:10,420 --> 00:37:12,480
 And I would just, I would talk to him.

829
00:37:12,480 --> 00:37:15,320
 I would ask his help.

830
00:37:15,320 --> 00:37:16,820
 I would seek his favor.

831
00:37:16,820 --> 00:37:20,940
 I would declare my trust and I would pray for his will.

832
00:37:20,940 --> 00:37:22,900
 Again and again and again,

833
00:37:22,900 --> 00:37:27,300
 I prayer walked the walls of Jericho down on that thing.

834
00:37:27,300 --> 00:37:32,900
 Which is why it was so shocking to me

835
00:37:32,900 --> 00:37:35,460
 when in the 11th hour,

836
00:37:35,460 --> 00:37:39,980
 the subject of my dreams

837
00:37:39,980 --> 00:37:44,540
 was like a rug pulled out from underneath me.

838
00:37:44,540 --> 00:37:48,260
 What I thought I was to attain

839
00:37:49,940 --> 00:37:52,140
 was ripped away from me.

840
00:37:52,140 --> 00:37:57,260
 And all I felt like I had were no more dreams,

841
00:37:57,260 --> 00:37:58,540
 yet only doubts.

842
00:37:58,540 --> 00:38:03,500
 Everything I'd longed for,

843
00:38:03,500 --> 00:38:05,320
 everything I prayed for,

844
00:38:05,320 --> 00:38:07,100
 everything I aimed for,

845
00:38:07,100 --> 00:38:10,260
 all that I had been trying to set myself up to acquire,

846
00:38:10,260 --> 00:38:12,380
 it was taken away from me in a moment.

847
00:38:12,380 --> 00:38:17,060
 And all I felt in that instance

848
00:38:18,660 --> 00:38:23,460
 was frustration and doubt and a faintness of heart

849
00:38:23,460 --> 00:38:26,100
 that led me to a place in my spirituality

850
00:38:26,100 --> 00:38:27,940
 I never thought I would find myself.

851
00:38:27,940 --> 00:38:32,740
 It was late one evening, about a month or so later,

852
00:38:32,740 --> 00:38:35,520
 that I was so depressed,

853
00:38:35,520 --> 00:38:37,860
 I'm sitting in the center of my driveway

854
00:38:37,860 --> 00:38:41,160
 at probably midnight.

855
00:38:41,160 --> 00:38:47,540
 And I have nothing left to say to God.

856
00:38:48,580 --> 00:38:50,180
 I've grumbled against Him,

857
00:38:50,180 --> 00:38:51,620
 I've warred with Him,

858
00:38:51,620 --> 00:38:53,900
 I've raged against the heavens,

859
00:38:53,900 --> 00:38:56,640
 I've expressed all my disappointment.

860
00:38:56,640 --> 00:39:02,140
 Some of you get what that feels like.

861
00:39:02,140 --> 00:39:07,080
 And yet as I sat in the center of my driveway,

862
00:39:07,080 --> 00:39:14,820
 I heard that still small voice

863
00:39:14,820 --> 00:39:17,220
 that is so unmistakably God

864
00:39:18,540 --> 00:39:20,300
 ask me this question,

865
00:39:20,300 --> 00:39:25,380
 are we still gonna go for walks?

866
00:39:25,380 --> 00:39:32,240
 All of my belief was broken,

867
00:39:32,240 --> 00:39:37,140
 but my bond was not.

868
00:39:37,140 --> 00:39:41,540
 No one can take away those

869
00:39:41,540 --> 00:39:43,940
 that are in relationship to God.

870
00:39:43,940 --> 00:39:45,380
 And no amount of doubt,

871
00:39:45,380 --> 00:39:46,620
 no amount of disappointment,

872
00:39:46,620 --> 00:39:50,660
 no amount of despair can wring you from His grip.

873
00:39:50,660 --> 00:39:54,100
 It is far too strong to ever let you go.

874
00:39:54,100 --> 00:39:54,940
 And you may feel,

875
00:39:54,940 --> 00:39:56,140
 I'm so far away though,

876
00:39:56,140 --> 00:39:58,820
 His arm is so very long.

877
00:39:58,820 --> 00:40:06,420
 He wants a real relationship with you.

878
00:40:06,420 --> 00:40:10,500
 Because He not only wants your soul,

879
00:40:10,500 --> 00:40:11,700
 He wants your heart.

880
00:40:14,460 --> 00:40:16,620
 For which God wants your heart.

881
00:40:16,620 --> 00:40:18,260
 And what we learn by the end of this text

882
00:40:18,260 --> 00:40:19,660
 is He wants it hot.

883
00:40:19,660 --> 00:40:25,140
 And He will pursue you in the coldness of doubt

884
00:40:25,140 --> 00:40:28,740
 until the flame of faith is rekindled again.

885
00:40:28,740 --> 00:40:33,100
 Is your heart burning tonight within you?

886
00:40:33,100 --> 00:40:34,420
 As you hear these words,

887
00:40:34,420 --> 00:40:38,300
 as this truth washes over your faint spirit,

888
00:40:38,300 --> 00:40:40,380
 is it burning again?

889
00:40:40,380 --> 00:40:43,220
 John Wesley, he famously said at his conversion

890
00:40:43,220 --> 00:40:46,580
 that his heart was gently warmed,

891
00:40:46,580 --> 00:40:48,460
 strangely warmed.

892
00:40:48,460 --> 00:40:54,620
 Friend, if your heart is warming here,

893
00:40:54,620 --> 00:40:59,060
 it's because Jesus is wanting here.

894
00:40:59,060 --> 00:41:01,020
 He is wanting for you.

895
00:41:01,020 --> 00:41:03,540
 And we have such confidence that that's the case

896
00:41:03,540 --> 00:41:05,260
 because what we know is when our hearts

897
00:41:05,260 --> 00:41:07,940
 have grown darker than doubt in the dead of our sins,

898
00:41:07,940 --> 00:41:11,020
 Jesus passionately pursued us anyways.

899
00:41:11,020 --> 00:41:12,260
 Like He walked towards us

900
00:41:12,260 --> 00:41:14,220
 and we had all walked away.

901
00:41:14,220 --> 00:41:16,380
 Like all of us, we had abandoned God.

902
00:41:16,380 --> 00:41:18,020
 Like sheep, we had gone astray.

903
00:41:18,020 --> 00:41:20,500
 And yet Jesus said, "You'll never outrun me.

904
00:41:20,500 --> 00:41:22,540
 "Doesn't matter how far away you walk from me,

905
00:41:22,540 --> 00:41:23,700
 "I'll chase you down.

906
00:41:23,700 --> 00:41:24,780
 "I'll race forward.

907
00:41:24,780 --> 00:41:27,580
 "I will pursue you still because you're my people.

908
00:41:27,580 --> 00:41:30,020
 "You may not want me, but I want you.

909
00:41:30,020 --> 00:41:31,620
 "I'm gonna bring you back.

910
00:41:31,620 --> 00:41:33,340
 "I'm gonna put you in my family

911
00:41:33,340 --> 00:41:35,660
 "because I'm a God, I'm a Savior.

912
00:41:35,660 --> 00:41:39,060
 "I'm a Lord that walks with those that walk away from me."

913
00:41:40,980 --> 00:41:44,100
 Jesus, He calmed our confusion with His words.

914
00:41:44,100 --> 00:41:46,620
 Like into the misery, in the madness of our sin,

915
00:41:46,620 --> 00:41:49,380
 He spoke the words of life.

916
00:41:49,380 --> 00:41:53,780
 Like He didn't just come to teach you some nice things,

917
00:41:53,780 --> 00:41:56,020
 to increase your academia,

918
00:41:56,020 --> 00:41:58,540
 to help you learn some new platitudes.

919
00:41:58,540 --> 00:42:02,220
 No, He came to speak into you life.

920
00:42:02,220 --> 00:42:08,260
 And He rekindled the flames of hearts grown cold.

921
00:42:09,500 --> 00:42:11,220
 How cold is a dead heart?

922
00:42:11,220 --> 00:42:14,580
 It's the coldest of all.

923
00:42:14,580 --> 00:42:19,220
 And yet Jesus said, "I will take their cold heart

924
00:42:19,220 --> 00:42:23,540
 "into my chest by dying their death

925
00:42:23,540 --> 00:42:26,580
 "that they might have my living heart

926
00:42:26,580 --> 00:42:29,820
 "and they might go free instead."

927
00:42:29,820 --> 00:42:37,460
 It does not matter the degree of your doubt.

928
00:42:38,460 --> 00:42:43,460
 What matters is the extent of His love.

929
00:42:43,460 --> 00:42:47,260
 He wants relationship.

930
00:42:47,260 --> 00:42:49,380
 Do you want it in return?

931
00:42:49,380 --> 00:42:50,460
 Let me pray for you.

932
00:42:50,460 --> 00:42:57,060
 God, I pray my friends here know

933
00:42:57,060 --> 00:43:04,180
 that you really want them.

934
00:43:05,940 --> 00:43:09,180
 It's impossible, God, for you to need us,

935
00:43:09,180 --> 00:43:10,900
 for you are all sufficient.

936
00:43:10,900 --> 00:43:16,020
 Therefore, God, for you to do what you've done

937
00:43:16,020 --> 00:43:17,500
 in the person of your Son

938
00:43:17,500 --> 00:43:23,700
 is a staggering declaration that you want all of us.

939
00:43:23,700 --> 00:43:26,140
 Not because of anything we've done,

940
00:43:26,140 --> 00:43:27,660
 not because of anything we've earned,

941
00:43:27,660 --> 00:43:29,260
 not because of anything we deserve, God,

942
00:43:29,260 --> 00:43:32,620
 but simply because you choose us.

943
00:43:33,940 --> 00:43:37,180
 I pray, God, that for those in this room

944
00:43:37,180 --> 00:43:40,100
 that feel like they are on the precipice of deconstruction,

945
00:43:40,100 --> 00:43:45,020
 that think doubt is all that dwells ahead

946
00:43:45,020 --> 00:43:48,420
 in their future, God, they might know it's not my doubt

947
00:43:48,420 --> 00:43:52,980
 that awaits for me in the future,

948
00:43:52,980 --> 00:43:57,340
 it's my Jesus that awaits for me instead.

949
00:43:57,340 --> 00:44:01,940
 We love you, God, and we sing to you now

950
00:44:01,940 --> 00:44:05,620
 the worship that is only worthy of you.

951
00:44:05,620 --> 00:44:10,740
 It's in Christ's name we pray, amen.

952
00:44:10,740 --> 00:44:12,380
 Hey, porch, you can stand to your feet.

953
00:44:12,380 --> 00:44:14,300
 We're gonna jump back into worship.

954
00:44:14,300 --> 00:44:17,340
 And for a God like that,

955
00:44:17,340 --> 00:44:20,780
 we're gonna blow the ever-loving roof off of this place.

956
00:44:20,780 --> 00:44:24,020
 (congregation cheering)

957
00:44:24,020 --> 00:44:27,740
 Like it is week two, it is the beginning of a year,

958
00:44:27,740 --> 00:44:32,740
 and yet we are going to go hard here in the final stretch.

959
00:44:32,740 --> 00:44:35,220
 We believe that God's worth it, amen?

960
00:44:35,220 --> 00:44:36,060
 - Amen.

961
00:44:36,060 --> 00:44:38,540
 - So we're gonna sing like we believe it.

